{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a6caf242-2d9d-4059-bdcf-78f444569b05","content":"With MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9, you can use **constructor injection** for `TestContext` and combine `[TestInitialize]` (which supports `async Task`) for async setup:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests : IAsyncDisposable, IDisposable\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private MyService _service;\n\n    // Constructor injection for TestContext + synchronous init\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        _service = new MyService();\n    }\n\n    // Async per-test initialization\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        await _service.ConnectAsync();\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Test starting\");\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task MyTest()\n    {\n        var result = await _service.DoWorkAsync();\n        Assert.IsNotNull(result);\n    }\n\n    // Async cleanup (preferred in modern MSTest)\n    public async ValueTask DisposeAsync()\n    {\n        await _service.DisconnectAsync();\n        GC.SuppressFinalize(this);\n    }\n\n    // Synchronous cleanup fallback\n    public void Dispose()\n    {\n        _service?.Dispose();\n        GC.SuppressFinalize(this);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **Constructor** — inject `TestContext`, do synchronous setup\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** — return `async Task` for async per-test setup\n- **`IAsyncDisposable`** — preferred cleanup pattern over `[TestCleanup]`\n- **`[ClassInitialize]`** / **`[ClassCleanup]`** — still available for one-time class-level setup if needed (must be `static`)","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7c550dff-d90f-479f-9444-fecb6ca3a043","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is using MSTest 3.8.2 with .NET 9.0. In modern MSTest (v3+), constructor injection for `TestContext` is supported. Let me provide the recommended pattern.\n\nIn MSTest v3+, the recommended way is:\n1. Constructor injection for `TestContext` (instead of the old property-based approach)\n2. `[TestInitialize]` for synchronous per-test setup\n3. `[TestInitialize]` also supports async (returns `Task`)\n4. `[ClassInitialize]` for one-time class setup\n5. You can also implement `IAsyncDisposable` / `IDisposable` for cleanup\n\n\n6. I'll show a concrete example demonstrating the constructor injection pattern with async initialization and proper cleanup.","outputTokens":628,"requestId":"581D:18C0B2:16975A1:180E897:6A0338AB"},"id":"790c0394-1185-4cec-9193-6866a471751b","timestamp":"2026-05-12T14:27:08.421Z","parentId":"6227c795-100d-4159-ba1e-b59706ac9911"}
